pageContext.claim: “And the press said we both had "large" rallies. One reporter in The New York Times actually said [O'Rourke's] rally was larger than mine.”
pageContext.analysis: The venue for this Trump rally in El Paso holds 6,500 people. Trump claimed his campaign got permission from the local fire department to accommodate 10,000 attendees. El Paso's fire chief denied that and said the venue was at capacity, with nearly 6,500 attendees. Still, an O'Rourke event organizer, citing law enforcement, said his rally drew 8,000. O'Rourke is from El Paso.
